Options Added: STG_OGG_PUMP_NAME and, DROP_JOURNAL_TABLE ALSO
*/ COMPONENT NAME: JKM MSSQL toMSSQL Consistent (OGG) COMPONENT VERSION: 11.1.2.5 AUTHOR: Oracle COMPATIBILITY: ODI 11.1.1 and above
DESCRIPTION - This JKM provides consistent journalizing procedures for MSSQL tables. - When starting the journal on a model, journals are automatically dropped from tables no longer in the set and new tables in the set are journalized. - If the table is already journalized with another model, its current journal data is lost and the table is transferred to the new CDC set. - When migrating Journalization on the model from another KM to this one, always stop the journal with the previous KM and restart with this one. - This KM provides transactional consistency. This means that when using this JKM, you do not have to define the order of the tables in the "Journalizing tables" tab of the Model Window.
- This JKM uses Oracle GoldenGate to capture data changes on the source tables from a MSSQL server. Unlike other CDC JKMs -This JKM journalize data in a "staging Oracle Database" not in the source server -"Start Journal" menu option will not actually start journaling. -"Start Journal" menu option creates the CDC framework ie : SNP_CDC Objects and J$ tables and views -"Start Journal" menu option creates Oracle GoldenGate parameters files and readme file -Users should not expect any journaled data until the operations in the readme file have been carried out.
-This JKM provides also oracle GoldenGate parameters files to performe the initial load. -This step is not mandatory, and the inial load can be perfomed with others utilities
REQUIREMENTS System Privileges - The default work schema must be granted the SELECT ANY TABLE privilege and the RESOURCE role. Oracle GoldenGate must be installed on both servers (source and staging)
Database set-up See the Oracle GoldenGate "Oracle Installation and Setup Guide" for more information on database requirements in particular the chapter Preparing the database for GoldenGate
OPTIONS (Refer to Option descriptions for more information on each option) VALIDATE: Adds extra steps to validate the usage of the KM
COMPATIBLE: Disables/Enables features depending on the version of the Oracle Database.
LIMITATIONS - When Starting the Journal, users should not expect any journaled data until the operations in the readme file have been carried out. - See the Oracle GoldenGate "Oracle Installation and Setup Guide" for more information

This option specifies a name to be used when naming Oracle GoldenGate Objects related to the source system such as: - Capture process - Source trail files - Definition files of the source tables
Please note that to avoid any conflict, this name should be unique across the entire Information System.
This name must not be longer than 5 characters and must contain only upper case letters and/or digits.
When SRC_SETUP_OGG_PROCESSES is set to No, this option still requires to be provided so that ODI knowns which capture setup to take the changes from. In such a case, the value of this option must match exactly the value that was provided when setting up the capture on the other Model.

A DSN defines an ODBC connection to a database. A DSN consists of a database name, the database directory, the database ODBC driver name, database authentication information, and other information depending on the database. External applications, such as GoldenGate, require a DSN, because a DSN enables an application to connect to a database without having to encode the required information within the application program.
